verses.text_plain: Moreover the spirit lifted me up, and brought me unto the east gate of the Lord’s house, which looketh eastward: and behold at the door of the gate five and twenty men; among whom I saw Jaazaniah the son of Azur, and Pelatiah the son of Benaiah, princes of the people.
verses.verse_html: 1Moreover the spirit lifted me up, and brought me unto the east gate of the Lord’s house, which looketh eastward: and behold at the door of the gate five and twenty men; among whom I saw Jaazaniah the son of Azur, and Pelatiah the son of Benaiah, princes of the people.

verses.text_plain: Then said he unto me, Son of man, these are the men that devise mischief, and give wicked counsel in this city:
verses.verse_html: 2Then said he unto me, Son of man, these are the men that devise mischief, and give wicked counsel in this city:

verses.text_plain: Which say, It is not near; let us build houses: this city is the caldron, and we be the flesh.
verses.verse_html:
3Which say, It is not near; let us build houses: this city is the caldron, and we be the flesh. ▼
▼ It is…: or, It is not for us to build houses near

footnotes.body_text: ▼ It is…: or, It is not for us to build houses near
footnotes.body_html: ▼ It is…: or, It is not for us to build houses near

verses.text_plain: Therefore prophesy against them, prophesy, O son of man.
verses.verse_html: 4Therefore prophesy against them, prophesy, O son of man.

verses.text_plain: And the Spirit of the Lord fell upon me, and said unto me, Speak; Thus saith the Lord; Thus have ye said, O house of Israel: for I know the things that come into your mind, every one of them.
verses.verse_html: 5And the Spirit of the Lord fell upon me, and said unto me, Speak; Thus saith the Lord; Thus have ye said, O house of Israel: for I know the things that come into your mind, every one of them.

verses.text_plain: Ye have multiplied your slain in this city, and ye have filled the streets thereof with the slain.
verses.verse_html: 6Ye have multiplied your slain in this city, and ye have filled the streets thereof with the slain.

verses.text_plain: Therefore thus saith the Lord God; Your slain whom ye have laid in the midst of it, they are the flesh, and this city is the caldron: but I will bring you forth out of the midst of it.
verses.verse_html: 7Therefore thus saith the Lord God; Your slain whom ye have laid in the midst of it, they are the flesh, and this city is the caldron: but I will bring you forth out of the midst of it.

tokens.text: but I will bring you forth

verses.text_plain: Ye have feared the sword; and I will bring a sword upon you, saith the Lord God.
verses.verse_html: 8Ye have feared the sword; and I will bring a sword upon you, saith the Lord God.

verses.text_plain: And I will bring you out of the midst thereof, and deliver you into the hands of strangers, and will execute judgments among you.
verses.verse_html: 9And I will bring you out of the midst thereof, and deliver you into the hands of strangers, and will execute judgments among you.

tokens.text: And I will bring you out

verses.text_plain: Ye shall fall by the sword; I will judge you in the border of Israel; and ye shall know that I am the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 10Ye shall fall by the sword; I will judge you in the border of Israel; and ye shall know that I am the Lord.

verses.text_plain: This city shall not be your caldron, neither shall ye be the flesh in the midst thereof; but I will judge you in the border of Israel:
verses.verse_html: 11This city shall not be your caldron, neither shall ye be the flesh in the midst thereof; but I will judge you in the border of Israel:

tokens.text: neither shall ye be the flesh

verses.text_plain: And ye shall know that I am the Lord: for ye have not walked in my statutes, neither executed my judgments, but have done after the manners of the heathen that are round about you.
verses.verse_html:
12And ye shall know that I am the Lord: for ye have not walked in my statutes, neither executed my judgments, but have done after the manners of the heathen that are round about you. ▼
▼ for ye…: or, which have not walked

footnotes.body_text: ▼ for ye…: or, which have not walked
footnotes.body_html: ▼ for ye…: or, which have not walked

verses.text_plain: And it came to pass, when I prophesied, that Pelatiah the son of Benaiah died. Then fell I down upon my face, and cried with a loud voice, and said, Ah Lord God! wilt thou make a full end of the remnant of Israel?
verses.verse_html: 13And it came to pass, when I prophesied, that Pelatiah the son of Benaiah died. Then fell I down upon my face, and cried with a loud voice, and said, Ah Lord God! wilt thou make a full end of the remnant of Israel?

tokens.text: And it came to pass, when I prophesied

verses.text_plain: Again the word of the Lord came unto me, saying,
verses.verse_html: 14Again the word of the Lord came unto me, saying,

verses.text_plain: Son of man, thy brethren, even thy brethren, the men of thy kindred, and all the house of Israel wholly, are they unto whom the inhabitants of Jerusalem have said, Get you far from the Lord: unto us is this land given in possession.
verses.verse_html: 15Son of man, thy brethren, even thy brethren, the men of thy kindred, and all the house of Israel wholly, are they unto whom the inhabitants of Jerusalem have said, Get you far from the Lord: unto us is this land given in possession.

verses.text_plain: Therefore say, Thus saith the Lord God; Although I have cast them far off among the heathen, and although I have scattered them among the countries, yet will I be to them as a little sanctuary in the countries where they shall come.
verses.verse_html: 16Therefore say, Thus saith the Lord God; Although I have cast them far off among the heathen, and although I have scattered them among the countries, yet will I be to them as a little sanctuary in the countries where they shall come.

tokens.text: Although I have cast them far off
yet will I be to them as a little

verses.text_plain: Therefore say, Thus saith the Lord God; I will even gather you from the people, and assemble you out of the countries where ye have been scattered, and I will give you the land of Israel.
verses.verse_html: 17Therefore say, Thus saith the Lord God; I will even gather you from the people, and assemble you out of the countries where ye have been scattered, and I will give you the land of Israel.

verses.text_plain: And they shall come thither, and they shall take away all the detestable things thereof and all the abominations thereof from thence.
verses.verse_html: 18And they shall come thither, and they shall take away all the detestable things thereof and all the abominations thereof from thence.

tokens.text: thither, and they shall take away

verses.text_plain: And I will give them one heart, and I will put a new spirit within you; and I will take the stony heart out of their flesh, and will give them an heart of flesh:
verses.verse_html: 19And I will give them one heart, and I will put a new spirit within you; and I will take the stony heart out of their flesh, and will give them an heart of flesh:

verses.text_plain: That they may walk in my statutes, and keep mine ordinances, and do them: and they shall be my people, and I will be their God.
verses.verse_html: 20That they may walk in my statutes, and keep mine ordinances, and do them: and they shall be my people, and I will be their God.

tokens.text: them: and they shall be my people
and I will be their God

verses.text_plain: But as for them whose heart walketh after the heart of their detestable things and their abominations, I will recompense their way upon their own heads, saith the Lord God.
verses.verse_html: 21But as for them whose heart walketh after the heart of their detestable things and their abominations, I will recompense their way upon their own heads, saith the Lord God.

verses.text_plain: Then did the cherubims lift up their wings, and the wheels beside them; and the glory of the God of Israel was over them above.
verses.verse_html: 22Then did the cherubims lift up their wings, and the wheels beside them; and the glory of the God of Israel was over them above.

verses.text_plain: And the glory of the Lord went up from the midst of the city, and stood upon the mountain which is on the east side of the city.
verses.verse_html: 23And the glory of the Lord went up from the midst of the city, and stood upon the mountain which is on the east side of the city.

verses.text_plain: Afterwards the spirit took me up, and brought me in a vision by the Spirit of God into Chaldea, to them of the captivity. So the vision that I had seen went up from me.
verses.verse_html: 24Afterwards the spirit took me up, and brought me in a vision by the Spirit of God into Chaldea, to them of the captivity. So the vision that I had seen went up from me.

verses.text_plain: Then I spake unto them of the captivity all the things that the Lord had shewed me.
verses.verse_html: 25Then I spake unto them of the captivity all the things that the Lord had shewed me.
